The memorandum delegates authority to the Secretary of Homeland Security, the Secretary of Health and Human Services, and the Secretary of the Treasury to submit expenditure information to Congress regarding national emergencies. It specifies that the Secretaries may consult with Congress to ensure accurate and prompt reporting. The memorandum also clarifies that it does not affect existing authorities or the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget. It must be implemented in accordance with applicable law and funding availability. Lastly, the Secretary of Homeland Security is instructed to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register. The memorandum is signed by President Joseph R. Biden Jr.